values: Man this quarter is going to blow big time.  I'm really disliking school right now, I have quite a hard and possibly very busy quarter ahead of me.  It just sucks so much. Robyn was here all last week so school wasn't so bad because I knew at the end of a shitty day she would be there to kiss and hold.  But now that she is gone this week has been depressing because I got really use to her being here and it was just so great, even if both were a little grumpy at times.  My head hurts and Josh disappeared earlier, and I have no idea where he went but I was hoping to get a start on our Graphics project, because I don't know much about Visual C++, well anything really. So I'm really lost.  Anyways, off to statistics, I hate that class... meh.

I hate this feeling that I get when I know I should be doing something so I start working on one thing but then just get frustrated so do something else and just keep circling until I'm not working on anything just thinking about what I have to do. So here is my list: 
1st 
Rough Draft Due on Monday for C Lit (got to page 3 but have writer's    block plus what I have so far is quite possibly shit) 
2nd
CSE 326 Written Homework due on Wednesday, thought about starting it but looked at the assignment and just didn't want to. 
3rd
CSE 303 Programming Homework due Friday, I'm actually close to being done, need to clean up code
4th
CSE 303 Societal Implications paper due Friday, it has to be 2-3 pages about a topic in computer science, but with writer's block I can't work on 2 things
5th
Final Draft of C Lit paper due on Friday
6th
I have two finals on Saturday, German and CSE326 which sucks I've never had two on one day, and that is stressful thinking about it. 

That's all I can think of right now, but I actually tried to do something healthy today so I went for a jog and when I got back I was just very tired, which made me unmovtivated, hence the reason I got very little done besides watching parts of movies.  The CS stuff I did last night and into the early morning.  The only thing I did today was to get a shitty start on my C Lit paper. Now I'm just circling thorugh my list of 5 (I haven't starting thinkign about the 6th yet) and I'm just going a little crazy thinking why am I sitting her doing nothing. And I was talking to Ashlee which cut down on my boredom but she went to clean her kitchen and then logged off at some point, which sucks, because now I don't feel like doing anything and I'm just sitting here. Hence the reason why I decided to update my journal at least it gives me something to do right? I wish I could write like this in my paper, come up with something good, but it just all comes out wrong or I can't think of anything that would be anywhere near correct. Anyways that's all for now.  Until next time, meh...

I had a crazy dream.. I think I'm going to start using lj for dream recorder or something.  So of course as most dreams things start to  fade as soon as I wake up but this much I do remember.  Robyn and I had just recently been married and we were moving into what seemed to be a new house, may have been an apartment.  But as we were unpacking a couple ladies walk in with a baby, and I'm thinking, "oh no, because I knew what they were going to ask". So we decided that we would watch after the baby while she was was out of town for a few days.  And it turns out that this lady is Natalie Portman and before she leaves she kisses me on both cheeks and then on the lips(closed mouth) and gives me a hug.  Sometime after she leaves, wolves appear ( I don't know whether someone left the door open or what) but they could smell the baby, so I had to grab the baby and run around while I was being chased by friggin' wolves, and at some point that all stopped. Then turns out that the baby is like Stewie... it was kind of an evolution, this baby was probably no more than 18 months maybe and started babbling, which suprised me some but then started being able to walk, and after a short amount of time started talking.  This was all quit weird, because this kid claimed to hate me, but whenever was scared would cuddle up with me.  For now that's all I really remember I just wanted to get that down.

I know I never update anymore. I guess that is just because the only times I used to update regularly is when I was feeling really shitty about life. And now I have my Robyn and life just isn't shitty anymore. It is amazing. I love her so much. I couldn't ask for a more carrying, beautiful, and all around wonderful girl. I'm so lucky to have her, and I miss her dearly.  Anyways, I just wanted to right down a few details of this crazy dream I had hoping that someone will read this and remind me of it for later. Well there was a pet shop where I was like walking around and this little kid and his mom were there. And she starting talking to me and I didn't know how she knew my name until I realized I was wearing a nametag and that my shirt had my name on it. (Not sure what the nametag was about) But she gives me some money and tells me to make the little boys day by letting him think that a stranger was nice enough to buy him a gift. After that there is all sorts of weird happens in the pet shop. Like a Croc eating the bunny the kid wanted and then pooping it out alive. And then the kid gets bit so the owner has to close up shop because she didn't have any signs warning of animals biting. Also part of my dream involved one of my 370 tas staying at my house which I'll go into more if someone brings this up or not in case I forget. Well I need to get to German. 
Auf Wiedersehen!

I figured it was about time that I really gave an update about what is going on in my life or something. School will be starting soon and I'm sure I'll have more reasons to update. More emotional turmoil or something along those lines. I guess I'm just more of a person to update when things are bad and I need to get things off my chest. But right now things are great so I had no reason to vent.  Well nothing much has been going on in my life. I went on a little road trip to Astoria, Oregon with Miles at some point. That was cool, it was nice to hang out with Miles. I've been engaged to the most wonderful girl in the world for over a month now. That is a pretty big piece of news in my life.  It is one of the greatest things to ever happen to me and Robyn makes me so very very happy. I love her so much and I'm not going back to school for a week and she is already gone, which makes me sad. It is hard seeing someone basically everyday, waking up to them being with you regularly then all of a sudden that is gone. She will be back Friday night my last night home, so that will be nice. I just love her so much and I feel like this year apart is going to be really hard. She is my everything, my strength, my love, she is a big part of my life and I hate being away from her. It is going to be hard on both of us. (hehe hard on)  But we'll make it, we have to so that we can someday spend the rest of our lives together. I just hope that our kids are as cute as Jayden. I love that kid he is such a cutie. Well I think that is about it for now. I love my Robyn, my wonderful fiance, damn I'm a lucky guy... yup yup :) Until next time, I'm naked around you.

Why does there have to be so much pressure to get a job? Why can't I just sit back and relax after 8 months of constant hell of school? Where every minute you are worrying about how your grades are going to turn out, because if you don't do well you won't get into the program you are looking to get into and then once you are in you have even more pressure to not drop your grades down too low so as to lose your ability to get a degree so that you can go off and get a career that most likely you are going to hate until the day you retire, then you will be too old to do anything that you'll actually enjoy.  Is that what I have to look forward to? Sounds fucking wonderful. Meh. But no I can't relax, if I want to have fun this summer I need to get a job, where I will work and most likely be too tired to do anything after work, so maybe I'll have the weekends off, is that when I have the fun to spend all the money I made that week with my minimum wage job, just to repeat it.. oh what fun that is. I know I'm being too dramatic, but damn I hate the fact that you have to work to make money, I wish you could do whatever you wanted without currency and everyone just did there part. If that was the case, hell I would go work some shitty job, as long as I could have my big screen tv, awesome computer, with fast porno loading speeds, and  a great wife to come home too. But we aren't that lucky.  I may have some of those things in my future, but certainly not all.   Fucking jobs... meh... don't want one, and don't necessarily need one... whatever..

Last weekend was pretty awesome, you can read Robyn's livejournal if you want to know the details.  I'm just amazed, everytime I see Robyn I truly fall more in love with her. Is that possible? Once I think that I'm as in love as I'll ever be something so small happens that makes me love her that much more.  It could just be a small moment in time where we're actually together; a kiss, a smile, a conversation, it doesn't matter what it is, but it hits me that I had just fallen more in love.  Love is a crazy thing it makes you forget about everything else, it makes the world a better place, it brings you to a state of happiness that you never thought you could reach.  That's why losing love is so hard and being away from the one you love is equally as hard.  I miss my Robyn beyond belief.  When I'm with her I don't have a care in the world, my life is perfect, being away from her is hell.  But it is that hell that makes the heaven when I am with her again.  A fitting description since she is an angel.  My guardian angel and my love for the rest of time.  I hope everyone finds true love, because it is amazing.  It makes you forget about the rest of attractive people out there, because no matter how attractive the girl is I find that she can't match up to the beauty, wonder, and greatness of my Robyn.  I love that, because other girls show me how lucky I am to have her. Well I should get back to working on my paper for Philosophy.  I know most of you don't care about what I said here because it is all lovey-dovey, but I just like to profess how I feel and isn't that what a journal's for? Yup yup :) Until next time, Robyn will always have my love, now and forever :)

Lets see it has been a while I guess.  Well I'm not going to describe my Spring break because you can check my Robyn's lj for the details of that.  All I can say is it was absolutely amazing to be with her :) I love that girl with all my heart and always will.  So my quarter ended well.  I got a 3.7 in Mechanical Engineering 231, a 4.0 in Psych 101, a 4.0 in Architecture 151, and a 3.8 in my Math 308 class. So it was pretty excited my cumm. gpa is now a 3.7 which has me excited.  So I did get offered a majors only Computer Sciene and Engineering (CSE) class. It is CSE 341 Programming languages.  We are using old ass (well maybe not old but primitive) languages.  They are basically functional and stupid, but the class should be alright. I'm also in Intro to Philosophy, which I think might suck because my graduate student teacher seems to like to push his ideas onto others. Next there is Psych 210 which is Human Sexuality which seems pretty interesting, I watched a bunch of people performing vaginal and oral sex along with masturbation yesterday in class. Then I have Architecture 251 Non-Western Arch, which for not being a Architecture major this is my 3rd class in that department but mostly because they are easy 3 credit classes. Well that's my quarter and that's all I got to say about that. Until next time,(What you do again last summer?), I was on Tatooine fighting Tuskan raiders, (How many of them did you kill), Like 50 of 'em, they kidnapped my mom, what the heck would you do in a situation like that?, (What kind of weapon did you use?), a freakin' lightsaber, whatdoya think!

Yes it is time for the much anticipated finals week (hits button to light up applause sign).  But seriously I hate this week, it is packing all the stress of the quarter into 5 days, not to mention the days before hand studying if you have early finals.  The way classes are made to be purely test based in the grading, this test can literally make or break your grade. It doesn't matter if you have been kicking ass all quarter (although it helps) one bad performance and your 4.0 turns into a 3.0 or lower. It is a sad fact of college that I think all of us students have to go through, but what can you do.  My finals aren't actually looking ot be too bad.  My math teacher pretty much has given us exactly what our final will look like, just like he did with the math midterm that I received a 96 out of 100 on. So that should be fine. My Mechanical Engineering class worries me a little because I hate the lecture part of that class, and finally Psychology which I have got a 100% or better on the last 3 tests shouldn't be a problem at all. It just sucks because right now I'm feeling kind of sick and that is never a good feeling.

         Last night I went to a Focus Group for an activity called Dawg Daze her at the UW, something I wasn't supposed to go to but Tiffany dragged me too. But it was cool to talk amongst a group even they were all Freshman or 1st year students here that transfered from another school.  I did get a 20 dollar gift card for the UW bookstore, although I can not use it to buy textbooks. How ironic. Anyways I'll be watching Jim Gaffigan on Friday hopefully, second time I will have gotten to see him this quarter. Oh and Dane Cook is going to be here April 4, 12 dollars for Students and 24 for non-students.  It is pretty bad ass, but I should probably buy my tickets before I end up missing out.  That's about it for now I believe, oh and I still miss Robyn, I can't write a post without saying that, that's how I feel.  I don't give a damn if people think I'm needy or clingy, I'm just a very affectionate person so deal with it, and don't give me shit for saying that I miss her, because put yourself in our shoes.  We are 300 miles away from each other and we are very cuddly people so it is hard, and I don't need your sympathy or do I need a lecture about being in a long distance relationship, because I knew what I was getting into. But I still have the right to say I miss her and I love her with all my heart because she is my angel. The previous statements are not specifically directed at anyone I just want to get that out there.  Until next time, you know you do you kill me well, you like it too and I can tell, you never stop until, my final breath is gone.

So I don't know what it is that gets me on this path, but it always seems to go about the same way.  First of all I'm like lets mess around, play Final Fantasy 7 all day (or something of that nature) then I think wait why do I keep putting of my homework. Then I realize I don't know how to do this, or I don't want to do this.  So then I mess around some more, let's watch Bad Santa.  Then I think now I'm getting stressed because I'm doing something besides homework.  That fucking guilty feeling you get even though you know there will be plenty of time to get your homework done but school has turned you into a homework machine, you must always be studying you can never have fun without feeling like shit for doing it. That's when I get to the point where I need my Robyn.  That's all I can think about... I want to talk to my Robyn.  I get distracted here and there, doing homework, playing a game, doing something but it always comes back.  Robyn is having fun right now, well at least I hope, but all I can think is, I wish she would come home.  But that isn't fair of me to think she has to have fun too, she has a life and I don't want her to feel bad that she wasn't here for me (don't feel bad hun) because she can't be by my side every step of the way.  She has already been there so much and I appreciate everything she does for me and I love her very much.  I just never know what to do, I feel so lost, like I have no one.... if Kylan was here I'd talk to him, but he is home this weekend... lucky me.... *sighs* Well I probably should go to bed soon... but I can't get myself to because there it is again, I need my Robyn....

Well on Friday after class I went to Subway, then to Trader Joe's with Kylan.  We were on our way to Safeway but we stopped by the Walgreens across the street first and ended up buying a bunch of 75% off Valentine's day stuff. Then I went over Safeway and bought some roses for Robyn.  I came back to my room and set up a little table with stuff from Walgreens and the floors, and had a little, "I love u" thing on my bulletin board :)  Then I played some Final Fantasy 7 in Kylan's room, until around 11:20ish or so Robyn called asking for directions to my dorm.  So when they got here I introduced Robyn and Brittany and we talked to Kylan a bit, and then we just held each other and enjoyed each others company :) 

Saturday morning, got up and had some cereal, lounged around then walked down to the U-Village and walked around the village.  Went over to Office Depot so I could buy a PCMCIA USB 2.0 card. After that we went over to Johnny Rockets for lunch, it is a pretty cool 50's style diner and our burgers were damn good. After that walked back to the dorm.  We were both kind of tired so we watched some Family guy and ended up falling asleep. Around 7 we went bowling with Kylan and Brittany.  That was pretty fun, and after bowling Robyn played some Dance Dance, and then Kylan and I did a versus match.  Kylan sucked real bad and was being silly about it.  After bowling Robyn and I went to IHOP alone because Kylan and Brittany are losers.  My omelette was very good, but I did make a bear using my pancakes, syrup, and a couple banana slices from Robyn's banana pancakes.  Then we came back here and just hung out talking to Kylan and Brittany for a while, because they were hanging out in Kylan's room.  Then we came back to my room and kissed and had fun :) 

Sunday morning woke up around 11 or so and we both showered. Around 3 Robyn's mom and her friend Karen showed up so that we could go see Phantom of the Opera in Bellevue. The movie was so incredible. I already had fallen in love with the music years ago and it was just so well done :)  Oh and Christine was a hottie, I checked it out and she is a year younger than me, that is cwazy :P Anyways, after the movie went to Karen's place for a little while then went to a Italian restaurant.  Not sure what it was called but it is North of UW in Shoreline.  We ate there with Karen's son and wife.  After dinner went back to Karen's and everyone sat around telling funny family stories of injuries.  Well I couldn't speak up because people were going on and on, so I just listened but it was nice.  Close to 11 we got back to the dorm when Karen's son and his wife dropped us off. We then watched The Notebook.  It was sad movie so Robyn and I both ended up crying and then started crying more because we were going to miss each other and it is always sad to know that we have to be apart again.  It was kind of cute us both crying but after a while we started laughing again, especially after I said, "You make me happy" while I was crying.  We just both started giggling :) Then we fell asleep pretty late.

Woke up this morning at 8:45 or 9 and just kissed and cuddled and had to say goodbye around 10.  I felt like an idiot because I forgot my husky card so was locked out of Mercer.  So I had to go to the Terry front desk to get a temporary key card.  Then I pretty much sat around and playing FFVII, and then Robyn got home and I talked to her for a while before she had to leave for rehearsel.  I already miss her.  She left this morning but it seems like we've been apart for months and it sucks, I hate being apart. But I know since I miss her and since it hurts so much that I am truly in love with her always and forever. That makes me so happy :) *hugs and kisses for my Robyn* So overall I had an incredible weekend.
Until next time, long distance relationships aren't for everyone, but Robyn and I will make it :)
